                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">The theory is that the malware wouldn&#x27;t execute in sandboxes for malware analysis, since the analysis environment will accept all connections from the sandbox.<p>So, if connection = successful, then we&#x27;re being analyzed and don&#x27;t execute.<p>If connection = unsuccessful, then we&#x27;re on a real workstation, execute!<p>Then the scheme fell apart when someone registered that domain, so all connections = successful and malware will not execute (but machine still infected).<span>
              </span><div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
