                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c88">Security researchers absolutely should have liability for poking malware in the wild on their own initiative.<p>If you&#x27;re a bomb enthusiast or researcher, you&#x27;d absolutely be liable if you tried to defuse a bomb without being requested to by the police. This is no different because of the potential for massive collateral damage. You want to see what happens when the domain is registered? Resolve the DNS on your own network.<p>It&#x27;s only when acting under government direction that you should be immunized from liability.<span>
