        <tr class='athing comtr ' id='14332038'><td>
            <table border='0'>  <tr>    <td class='ind'><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="200"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks"><center><a id='up_14332038' href='vote?id=14332038&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D14330547'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead">
          <a href="user?id=jldugger" class="hnuser">jldugger</a> <span class="age"><a href="item?id=14332038">1 day ago</a></span> <span id="unv_14332038"></span><span class="par"></span> <a class="togg" n="7" href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return toggle(event, 14332038)"></a>          <span class='storyon'></span>
                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">Folks disagree with you for the same reason they pass [good samaritan laws](<a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;en.wikipedia.org&#x2F;wiki&#x2F;Good_Samaritan_law" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;en.wikipedia.org&#x2F;wiki&#x2F;Good_Samaritan_law</a>): intent.<p>A bit more econo-mathematically stated: we expect more good than bad to come by us if we indemnify them from whatever liability they may have had by accidentally triggering the mechanism. Perhaps because there&#x27;s more smart people outside the government than inside it, just as there are more smart people outside any corporation than inside it, or anywhere really, because human ingenuity is widely distributed.<span>
              </span><div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
                      <u><a href="reply?id=14332038&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D14330547%2314332038">reply</a></u>
                  </font>
