                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">It was explained quite clearly in the article. Sandboxed environments will generally have a catch all that replies to any IP requests with a sinkhole server. To prevent analysis, it&#x27;d do a lookup to a known unregistered domain and if it got back an IP address (which should not happen except in the sandbox with an unregistered domain) then it quits because it assumes it&#x27;s sandboxed and being analyzed.<span>
              </span><div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
