        <tr class='athing comtr ' id='14332955'><td>
            <table border='0'>  <tr>    <td class='ind'><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="80"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks"><center><a id='up_14332955' href='vote?id=14332955&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D14330547'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead">
          <a href="user?id=pbhjpbhj" class="hnuser">pbhjpbhj</a> <span class="age"><a href="item?id=14332955">23 hours ago</a></span> <span id="unv_14332955"></span><span class="par"></span> <a class="togg" n="1" href="javascript:void(0)" onclick="return toggle(event, 14332955)"></a>          <span class='storyon'></span>
                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">You can tell it&#x27;s _not_ <i>Cymraeg</i> because of the &quot;j&quot;s.<p>Despite Jones being the stereotypical name for people in Wales, the old Welsh language, Cymraeg, doesn&#x27;t have a J, nor have Z, K, V, X (IIRC). Jones is an English loanword, brought over apparently with the Norman conquest (though derived from Hebrew).<p>The modern language of Wales is of course British English with a ~100% use rate; <i>Cymraeg</i> still has an approx 8% (but falling) of the population who say when surveyed that they can speak it fluently, however.<p>Yeah, I&#x27;m terrible at parties.<span>
              </span><div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
                      <u><a href="reply?id=14332955&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D14330547%2314332955">reply</a></u>
                  </font>
      </div></td></tr>
      </table></td></tr>
